1          /*------------------------------------------------------------------*
2          | PROGRAM NAME : rename_study_domains_cli20260320.sas
3          | SHORT DESC   : Standardizes SAS and XPT dataset names by removing
4          |                suffixes (e.g., AE_PLACEBO to AE) and placing
5          |                renamed copies in DAC_<ParentFolderName> or DAC_XPT subfolders
6          *------------------------------------------------------------------*
7          | CREATED BY   : DAC Development Team
8          | DATE CREATED : 2026-05-08
9          | VERSION      : 1.4
10         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
11         | VERSION UPDATES:
12         | 2026-05-08: Initial CLI release (v1.0)
13         |   - Added SYSPARM parsing for input and output directories
14         |   - Standardizes dataset names by keeping only the prefix before
15         |     the first underscore (e.g., AE_PLACEBO -> AE)
16         |   - Copies SAS7BDAT datasets to DAC_SAS subfolder when any file
17         |     in the input directory has a non-standard (suffixed) name
18         |   - Copies XPT datasets to DAC_XPT subfolder when any XPT file
19         |     in the input directory has a non-standard name
20         |   - Files without underscores are copied unchanged to the new
21         |     folder so the folder is a complete, self-consistent set
22         | 2026-05-12: SAS7BDAT logic updated to match OriginalSAS (v1.1)
23         |   - Replaced Windows DIR-based file listing with libname +
24         |     dictionary.tables discovery (aligns with
25         |     rename_study_domains_ZRlocalCopy.sas)
26         |   - ALL datasets are now copied to DAC_SAS first via proc copy,
27         |     then datasets with suffixes are renamed in-place in DAC_SAS
28         |     using proc datasets change (same approach as original script)
29         |   - Standard name derived with scan(memname, 1, '_') -- identical
30         |     to the original script
31         | 2026-05-12: Fix standard name extraction (v1.2)
32         |   - Changed scan position from 1 to -1 so the domain name is taken
2                                           The SAS System               11:43 Wednesday, May 20, 2026

33         |     from the LAST token after the final underscore (e.g.
34         |     BERKELEY_AE -> AE).  Using position 1 caused all datasets to
35         |     map to the study prefix (e.g. BERKELEY), triggering a duplicate-
36         |     name collision for every dataset in the library.
37         | 2026-05-19: Dynamic SAS output folder naming (v1.3)
38         |   - SAS output folder is now named DAC_<ParentFolderName> where
39         |     ParentFolderName is the leaf segment of the input directory
40         |     (e.g. if input is C:\data\rawdata, folder becomes DAC_rawdata).
41         |   - Handles both Windows backslash and Unix forward slash separators.
42         | 2026-05-19: Fixed dcreate return-value check (v1.4)
43         |   - Replaced `%if &_rc = %then` with `%if %length(&_rc) = 0 %then`
44         |     for both directory-creation guards (DAC_<ParentFolderName> and
45         |     DAC_XPT). dcreate returns the new directory name on success,
46         |     causing %EVAL to abort with a numeric-operand error when the
47         |     directory was successfully created.
48         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
49         | PURPOSE
50         | Checks SAS (.sas7bdat) and XPT (.xpt) datasets in the specified
51         | input directory and standardizes their names by removing
52         | study-specific suffixes (e.g., converting AE_PLACEBO to AE).
53         | When any dataset requires renaming, ALL datasets of that type are
54         | copied with standardized names to a new subfolder:
55         |   - DAC_<ParentFolderName> for .sas7bdat files
56         |   - DAC_XPT for .xpt files
57         | This ensures that subsequent pipeline scripts operate on a
58         | complete, consistently named set of datasets.
59         |
60         | Naming rule: the standard name is the portion of the dataset name
61         | after the last underscore (scan(memname, -1, '_')).  E.g.:
62         |   BERKELEY_AE   -> AE
63         |   BERKELEY_SUPPAE -> SUPPAE
64         |   CM          -> CM  (unchanged; no folder created for this alone)
65         |
66         | 1.1: REQUIRED SYSPARM PARAMETERS (pipe-delimited)
67         | INPUT_DIRECTORY  = Path to folder containing .sas7bdat or .xpt
68         |                    files to be renamed
69         | OUTPUT_DIRECTORY = Path to folder where DAC_<ParentFolderName>
70         |                    and/or DAC_XPT subfolders will be created.
71         |                    Must exist prior to execution.
72         |
73         | USAGE:
74         |   sas -sysparm "input_directory|output_directory"
75         |       -sysin rename_study_domains_cli20260320.sas
76         |
77         | OUTPUT STRUCTURE:
78         |   output_directory\
79         |   ├── DAC_<ParentFolderName>\  - Standardized SAS7BDAT datasets
80         |   │                              (created only when any .sas7bdat
81         |   │                               dataset has a non-standard suffix)
82         |   └── DAC_XPT\   - Standardized XPT datasets
83         |                     (created only when any .xpt file has
84         |                      a non-standard suffix)
85         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
86         | OPERATING SYSTEM COMPATIBILITY
3                                           The SAS System               11:43 Wednesday, May 20, 2026

87         | SAS v9.4 or Higher: Yes
88         | Windows:            Yes
89         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
90         | NOTES
91         | - If two input datasets share the same standard name (e.g.,
92         |   AE_PLACEBO and AE_TREATMENT both map to AE), a WARNING is
93         |   issued and those datasets are skipped.  Resolve naming conflicts
94         |   in the source data before running the pipeline.
95         | - For XPT files the script queries the SAS transport library to
96         |   obtain the actual member name inside each file.  SAS XPT
97         |   format limits member names to 8 characters.
98         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
99         | EXAMPLES
100        |
101        | Standardize SAS dataset names:
102        |   sas -sysparm "C:\data\input|C:\data\output"
103        |       -sysin rename_study_domains_cli20260320.sas
104        |
105        | Standardize XPT dataset names:
106        |   sas -sysparm "C:\data\xpt_files|C:\data\output"
107        |       -sysin rename_study_domains_cli20260320.sas
108        *------------------------------------------------------------------*/
109        
110        /* ----------------------------------------------------------------
111           Helper macro: copy one XPT file to DAC_XPT with a standardized
112           member name.  Called via %nrstr() inside a DATA step CALL EXECUTE
113           so that each file is processed sequentially after the driving
114           DATA step completes.
115        
116           Parameters:
117             inpath        - full path to the source .xpt file
118             outpath       - full path for the destination .xpt file
119             standard_name - desired (standardized) SAS dataset name
120        ---------------------------------------------------------------- */
121        %macro _copy_xpt_file(inpath=, outpath=, standard_name=);
122        
123            /* Open source XPT with SAS transport engine */
124            libname _xinlib xport "&inpath";
125        
126            /* Get the actual member name stored inside the XPT file */
127            proc sql noprint;
128                select memname into :_xpt_memname trimmed
129                from dictionary.tables
130                where libname = '_XINLIB';
131            quit;
132        
133            %if %length(&_xpt_memname) = 0 %then %do;
134                %put WARNING: No dataset found in XPT file: &inpath -- skipping.;
135                libname _xinlib clear;
136                %return;
137            %end;
138        
139            %let _xpt_memname_lc = %lowcase(&_xpt_memname);
140            %let _std_lc         = %lowcase(&standard_name);
4                                           The SAS System               11:43 Wednesday, May 20, 2026

141        
142            %if %upcase(&_xpt_memname) ne %upcase(&standard_name) %then %do;
143                /* Copy internal dataset to WORK under the standard name */
144                data work.&_std_lc;
145                    set _xinlib.&_xpt_memname_lc;
146                run;
147        
148                libname _xinlib clear;
149        
150                /* Write the WORK dataset to the new XPT file */
151                libname _xoutlib xport "&outpath";
152                proc copy in=work out=_xoutlib;
153                    select &_std_lc;
154                run;
155                libname _xoutlib clear;
156        
157                /* Clean up temporary WORK dataset */
158                proc datasets lib=work nolist;
159                    delete &_std_lc;
160                quit;
161            %end;
162            %else %do;
163                /* Name already matches standard; copy file as-is */
164                libname _xoutlib xport "&outpath";
165                proc copy in=_xinlib out=_xoutlib; run;
166                libname _xinlib  clear;
167                libname _xoutlib clear;
168            %end;
169        
170        %mend _copy_xpt_file;
171        
